**14-Year-Old Colombian Math Prodigy Heads to Singapore**
Sebastián Trujillo, a 14-year-old student from Cali, Colombia, has qualified to represent his country at the 19th International Mathematical Olympiad (SIMOC) in Singapore, scheduled to take place from July 17 to July 21, 2026. Trujillo's journey began in 2025 during regional math competitions, where he achieved the top result for his grade, followed by a first-place finish in the National Math Olympiads. His success led to international recognition, including a bronze medal at the virtual Olimpri Olympiad from Mexico and a silver medal at the SASMO Olympiad in Asia. Trujillo, who aims to inspire other children, noted that he enjoys the problem-solving aspect of mathematics over simple calculation. The family is seeking community support to raise approximately 35 million Colombian pesos to cover the costs of the trip. The family has provided a WhatsApp contact number (318 608 3885) for those wishing to contribute to the initiative.
