**2026 Junior High School Exam Results: 712 Students Score 5A with Writing Level 6**
According to the National Center for Assessment (心測中心), the 115th Junior High School Basic Competency Test (國中教育會考) results were announced on June 5, 2026. 712 students achieved a perfect score of 5A with a Level 6 in writing, representing 0.4% of all test-takers, an increase of 171 students compared to last year. Additionally, 16,293 students achieved 5A, a figure similar to the previous year. Conversely, 1,490 students (5.82% of the total) received 5C (all subjects marked 'Need Improvement'), an increase of 491 students from the previous year, though the percentage remains below 6%. The test utilizes a 'criterion-referenced' system to categorize performance into three levels: 'Advanced' (精熟), 'Basic' (基礎), and 'Need Improvement' (待加強). Zeng Fen-lan, Deputy Director of the Center, explained that the 'Advanced' threshold corresponds to answering approximately 77% to 91% of questions correctly, while the 'Basic' threshold is around 37% to 40%. For the Chinese subject specifically, 36 correct answers out of 42 (85.71%) are required for 'Advanced', and 17 correct answers (40.48%) for 'Basic'. In terms of subject performance, Mathematics had the highest 'Advanced' rate at 24.56%, followed by Chinese at 24.29% and English at 23.37%, while Natural Sciences had the lowest at 17.41%. The Taiwan Normal University Center for Assessment confirmed that results are available online at cap.rcpet.edu.tw starting June 5, 2026, at 8:00 AM.
